    "(76)Substituting ( 75) and ( 76) into (74), we have∥ F (θ 1, ω 1, µ 1, V 1) -F (θ 2, ω 2, µ 2, V 2)∥ ≤ 1 + τ log |A| + (1 + γ)B V + (4 + 8 log |A|)τ (1 -γ) 3 ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + 2L r ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + 2(1 + γ)∥V 1 -V 2 ∥ + B F 1 -γ L P ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + ∥ω 1 -ω 2 ∥ = 1 + τ log |A| + (1 + γ)B V + (4 + 8 log |A|)τ (1 -γ) 3 + B F 1 -γ ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + 2L r + B F L P 1 -γ ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + B F 1 -γ ∥ω 1 -ω 2 ∥ + 4∥V 1 -V 2 ∥.This obviously leads to the claimed result by settingL F = max 1 + τ log |A| + (1 + γ)B V + (4+8 log |A|)τ (1-γ) 3 + B F 1-γ, 2L r + B F L P 1-γ, B F 1-γ, 4.The Lipschitz continuity of D can be shown using almost identical steps, which we will skip.For H, we can adopt a similar argument∥ H(π 1, ω 1, µ 1) -H(π 2, ω 2, µ 2)∥ ≤ ∥E s∼ν π 1, ϕω 1, µ 1 [H(µ 1, s) -H(µ 2, s)]∥ + B H s d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s) ≤ ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + s d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s)P π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 (• | s) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s)P π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 (• | s) ≤ ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + 1 1 -γ L P ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + ∥ω 1 -ω 2 ∥ ≤ L H (∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + ∥ω 1 -ω 2 ∥ + ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥),with L H = max{ L P 1-γ, 1}.",
    "For Ḡf, we again split ∥ Ḡf (θ 1, ω 1, µ 1, V 1)-Ḡf (θ 2, ω 2, µ 2, V 2)∥ into two parts and invoke Lemma 2∥ Ḡf (θ 1, ω 1, µ 1, V 1) -Ḡf (θ 2, ω 2, µ 2, V 2)∥ ≤ ∥E s∼d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ 1 ρ,a∼π θ 1 (•|s),b∼ϕω 1 (•|s),s ′ ∼P µ 1 (•|s,a,b) [G f (θ 1, µ 1, V 1, s, a, b, s ′) -G f (θ 2, µ 2, V 2, s, a, b, s ′)]∥ + B G s,s ′ d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s)P π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 (s ′ | s) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s)P π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 (s ′ | s) ≤ r f (s, a, b, µ 1) -r f (s, a, b, µ 2) + τ E(π θ1, s) -τ E(π θ2, s) + γV 1 (s ′) -γV 2 (s ′) -V 1 (s) + V 2 (s)) + B G 1 -γ L P ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + ∥ω 1 -ω 2 ∥ ≤ (4 + 8 log |A|)τ (1 -γ) 3 + B G 1 -γ ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + (L r + B G L P 1 -γ)∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + B G 1 -γ ∥ω 1 -ω 2 ∥ + 2∥V 1 -V 2 ∥.Similarly,∥ Ḡl (ω 1, µ 1, V 1) -Ḡl (ω 2, µ 2, V 2)∥ ≤ ∥E s∼d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ 1 ρ,a∼π θ 1 (•|s),b∼ϕω 1 (•|s),s ′ ∼P µ 1 (•|s,a,b) [G l (µ 1, V 1, s, a, b, s ′) -G l (µ 2, V 2, s, b, s ′)]∥ + B G s,s ′ d π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 ρ (s)P π θ 1, ϕω 1 µ1 (s ′ | s) -d π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 ρ (s)P π θ 2, ϕω 2 µ2 (s ′ | s) ≤ r l (s, b, µ 1) -r l (s, b, µ 2) + γV 1 (s ′) -γV 2 (s ′) -V 1 (s) + V 2 (s)) + B G 1 -γ L P ∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + ∥ω 1 -ω 2 ∥ ≤ B G 1 -γ ∥θ 1 -θ 2 ∥ + (L r + B G L P 1 -γ)∥µ 1 -µ 2 ∥ + B G 1 -γ ∥ω 1 -ω 2 ∥ + 2∥V 1 -V 2 ∥.",
    "■ D.5 Proof of Lemma 5Within the proof of Lemma 5, we use the shorthand notationy k = μk -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k) + ξ k H(π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk), ω k, μk).As the operator µ ⋆ is Lipschitz, we know from the mean-value theorem that there existsω z k+1 = zω k + (1 -z)ω k+1 for some scalar z ∈ [0, 1] such that µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k+1) -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k) = ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) ⊤ (ω k+1 -ω k) = ζ k ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k, s k, b k, s ′ k) = ζ k ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k) + ζ k ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k, s k, b k, s ′ k) -D(ω k, μk, Vl,k).This impliesE[⟨μ k -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k) + ξ k H(π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk), ω k, μk), µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k+1) -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k)⟩] = ζ k E[⟨y k, ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k)⟩] + ζ k E[⟨y k, ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k, s k, b k, s ′ k) -D(ω k, μk, Vl,k) ⟩] = ζ k E[⟨y k, ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k)⟩] + ζ k E[⟨y k, ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) -∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k, s k, b k, s ′ k) -D(ω k, μk, Vl,k) ⟩] + ζ k E[⟨y k, ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k) ⊤ E[D(ω k, μk, Vl,k, s k, b k, s ′ k) -D(ω k, μk, Vl,k) | F k-1]⟩] = ζ k E[⟨y k, ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k)⟩] + ζ k E[⟨y k, ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) -∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k, s k, b k, s ′ k) -D(ω k, μk, Vl,k) ⟩].",
    "(77)To bound the first term of (77), note that by Assumption 2 and the fact that the softmax operator is 1-Lipschitzζ k ⟨y k, ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k)⟩ ≤ Lζ k ∥y k ∥∥ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k)∥ ≤ (1 -δ)ξ k 16 ∥y k ∥ 2 + 4L 2 ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ∥ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k)∥ 2 ≤ (1 -δ)ξ k 16 ∥y k ∥ 2 + 8L 2 ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ∥ D(ω k, µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k), V ϕω k,µ ⋆ (ϕω k) l)∥ 2 + 8L 2 ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ∥ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k) -D(ω k, µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k), V ϕω k,µ ⋆ (ϕω k) l)∥ 2 ≤ (1 -δ)ξ k 16 ∥y k ∥ 2 + 8L 2 ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ∥∇ ω J l (ϕ ω k, µ) | µ=µ ⋆ (ϕω k) ∥ 2 + 16L 2 L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ∥μ k -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k)∥ 2 + 16L 2 L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ∥ Vl,k -V ϕω k,µ ⋆ (ϕω k) l ∥ 2 ≤ (1 -δ)ξ k 16 ∥y k ∥ 2 + 8L 2 η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ∥∇ ω J l (ϕ ω k, µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k))∥ 2 + 16L 2 L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ∥μ k -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k)∥ 2 + 32L 2 L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ∥V ϕω k,μ k l -V ϕω k,µ ⋆ (ϕω k) l ∥ 2 + 32L 2 L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ∥ Vl,k -V ϕω k,μ k l ∥ 2 ≤ (1 -δ)ξ k 16 ∥y k ∥ 2 + 8L 2 η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ε ϕ k + 48L 2 L 2 V L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ε µ k + 32L 2 L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k ε V l,k,(78)where the fifth inequality follows from Assumption 6.To bound the second term of (77),ζ k E[⟨y k, ∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) -∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k) ⊤ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k, s k, b k, s ′ k) -D(ω k, μk, Vl,k) ⟩] ≤ 2B D ζ k E[∥y k ∥∥∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω z k+1) -∇ ω µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k)∥] ≤ 2B D Lζ k E[∥y k ∥∥ϕ ω z k+1 -ϕ ω k ∥] ≤ 2B D Lζ k E[∥y k ∥∥ϕ ω k+1 -ϕ ω k ∥] ≤ 2B 2 D Lζ 2 k E[∥y k ∥] ≤ B 2 D Lζ 2 k E[∥y k ∥ 2] + B 2 D Lζ 2 k.(79)Substituting ( 78) and ( 79) into ( 77),E[⟨μ k -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k) + ξ k H(π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk), ω k, μk), µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k+1) -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k)⟩] ≤ (1 -δ)ξ k 16 E[∥y k ∥ 2] + 8L 2 η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k E[ε ϕ k] + 48L 2 L 2 V L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k E[ε µ k] + 32L 2 L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k E[ε V l,k] + B 2 D Lζ 2 k E[∥y k ∥ 2] + B 2 D Lζ 2 k ≤ (1 -δ)ξ k 8 E[∥y k ∥ 2] + 8L 2 η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k E[ε ϕ k] + 48L 2 L 2 V L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k E[ε µ k] + 32L 2 L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -δ)ξ k E[ε V l,k] + B 2 D Lζ 2 k,where the last inequality follows from the step size conditionsζ k ≤ 1 and ζ k ξ k ≤ 1-δ 16B 2 D L. ■ D.6 Proof of Lemma 6Within the proof of Lemma 6, we denote x k = (ϕ ω k, μk).",
    "By the law of total expectation,-E[⟨∇ x J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk) -∇ x J f (π, ϕ ω k, μk) | π=π ⋆ (ϕω k,μ k), x k+1 -x k ⟩] = -E[⟨∇ x J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk) -∇ x J f (π, ϕ ω k, μk) | π=π ⋆ (ϕω k,μ k), E ζ k D(ω k, μk, Vl,k, s k, b k, s ′ k) ξ k H(μ k, sk) F k-1 ⟩] = E[⟨∇ x J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk) -∇ x J f (π, ϕ ω k, μk) | π=π ⋆ (ϕω k,μ k), ζ k D(ω k, μk, Vl,k) ξ k H(π θ k, ω k, μk) ⟩] ≤ (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k 4|S|L 2 V E[∥∇ x J f (π θ k, ϕ ω k, μk) -∇ x J f (π, ϕ ω k, μk) | π=π ⋆ (ϕω k,μ k) ∥ 2] + |S|L 2 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k)∥ 2] + |S|L 2 V ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥ H(π θ k, ω k, μk)∥ 2] ≤ (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k 4|S| E[∥π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk) -π θ k ∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥ D(ω k, µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k), V ϕω k,µ ⋆ (ϕω k) l)∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥ D(ω k, μk, Vl,k) -D(ω k, µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k), V ϕω k,µ ⋆ (ϕω k) l)∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥ H(π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk), ω k, μk) -H(π ⋆ (ϕ ω k), ω k, µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k))∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥ H(π θ k, ω k, μk) -H(π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk), ω k, μk)∥ 2] ≤ (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k 4|S| E[∥π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk) -π θ k ∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥∇ ω J l (ϕ ω k, µ) | µ=µ ⋆ (ϕω k) ∥ 2] + 4|S|L 2 V L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥μ k -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k)∥ 2] + 4|S|L 2 V L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥ Vl,k -V ϕω k,µ ⋆ (ϕω k) l ∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V L 2 D ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k • L 2 H E[∥μ k -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k)∥ 2 + L 2 ∥μ k -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k) ∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V L 2 D ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k • L 2 H E[∥π ⋆ (ϕ ω k,μ k) -π θ k ∥ 2] ≤ (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k 4|S| E[∥π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk) -π θ k ∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥∇ ω J l (ϕ ω k, µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k))∥ 2] + 4|S|L 2 V L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥μ k -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k)∥ 2] + 8|S|L 2 V L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥V ϕω k,μ k l -V ϕω k,µ ⋆ (ϕω k) l ∥ 2] + 8|S|L 2 V L 2 D ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥ Vl,k -V ϕω k,μ k l ∥ 2] + 4|S|L 2 L 2 V L 2 D L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥μ k -µ ⋆ (ϕ ω k)∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V L 2 D L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥π ⋆ (ϕ ω k,μ k) -π θ k ∥ 2] ≤ (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k 4|S| E[∥π ⋆ (ϕ ω k, μk) -π θ k ∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V L 2 D L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[∥π ⋆ (ϕ ω k,μ k) -π θ k ∥ 2] + 2|S|L 2 V η 2 2 ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε ϕ k] + 16|S|L 2 L 4 V L 2 D L 2 H ξ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε µ k] + 8|S|L 2 V ζ 2 k (1 -γ)τ 2 ρ 3 min p 2 min α k E[ε V l,k],(80)where the second inequality follows from the fact that H(π ⋆ (ϕ), ω k, µ ⋆ (ϕ)) = 0, and the last inequality simplifies and combines terms under the step size conditionζ k ξ k ≤ LL H. ■ D.7 Proof of Lemma 7Within the proof of this lemma, we employ the shorthand notationx k = [θ k, ω k, μk], ℓ(x k) = V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f, andy k = Vf,k -V π θ k,ϕω k, μk f + β k Ḡf (θ k, ω k, μk, Vf,k).The value function is smooth, i.e."
